ZCZC GE66
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SATURDAY TO TUESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 302300 UTC
AT THE START OF THE PERIOD A LARGE AREA OF LOW PRESSURE IS CENTRED 994
N OF FAEROES WITH A CYCLONIC INFLUENCE ACROSS PORTPATRICK AND CULLERCOATS
WHILST THE AZORES HIGH 1033 EXTENDS A RIDGE ACROSS MOST SERN UK SEA WATERS.
OVERNIGHT AND THROUGH SUNDAY THE LOW CONTINUES TO DEEPEN REACHING 991 BY
MIDDAY. THERE IS LITTLE CHANGE TO THE SYNOPTIC PATTERN THROUGH THE REMAINDER
OF SATURDAY. ON SUNDAY THE LOW STARTS TO FILL AND DRIFT NWARDS WHILST THE
AZORES HIGH BUILDS SLTLY AND ALSO DRIFTS NWARDS TOWARDS SHANNON. BY THE END
OF THE PERIOD THE HIGH EXERTS AN ANTICYCLONIC INFLUENCE ACROSS PORTPATRICK
AND NITON WHILST A SHALLOW TROUGH MOVS EWARDS THROUGH CULLERCOATS AS THE
LOW MOVS TO THE N NORWAY COAST. STRG TO NEAR GALE WINDS ARE LIKELY ACROSS
FAIR ISLE ON MONDAY MORNING BEFORE SPREADING EWARDS ACROSS VIKING N UTSIRE
FORTIES AND CROMARTY THEN EASING OVERNIGHT
